 make the pickling vinegar, put the whole spices in a medium saucepan. Toast over a low heat until they begin to smell aromatic. Add the dried chilli flakes last, as these can easily catch.\nAdd the bay, pour in all of the vinegar and sugar, let it dissolve, and bring to a simmer.\nPour the hot vinegar over the shallots and seal while hot. Ready to eat in 1 month, or longer, if you like.", "act_image": "https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/spiced-pickled-shallots-546ae87.jpg", "act_nutrients": {"calories": "26 calories", "carbohydrateContent": "4 grams carbohydrates", "sugarContent": "4 grams sugar", "fiberContent": "2 grams fiber", "proteinContent": "1 grams protein", "sodiumContent": "0.9 milligram of sodium"}}